The paper proposes a system for autonomous aerial cinematography that involves visual pose estimation, 3D mapping, and camera motion planning. These topics are all related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artistic guidelines in the camera motion planning, which suggests a potential connection to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of real-time algorithms, which could indicate a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for efficient computation.
